#MEM id=competitor-analysis source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/custom/competitor-analysis/SKILL.md
M|competitor-analysis|name: cp-analysis
M|competitor-analysis|description: Kai's structured framework for turning YVON cp scrape data into actionable competitive intelligence. Covers data ingestion from /api/cp-*, scoring, gap analysis, and opportunity identific
M|competitor-analysis|version: 1.0.0
M|competitor-analysis|YVON scrapes cp cnt and intelligence via multiple routes (`/api/cp-cnt`, `/api/cp-intelligence`, `/api/auto-cp`, `/api/cp-exploit`, `/api/cp-pl`). This skill defines how Kai transforms that raw data i
M|competitor-analysis|Data without structure is noise. This skill makes it signal.
M|competitor-analysis|- When Stark asks "what are cp doing?"
M|competitor-analysis|- When a new cp scrape completes in `/api/cp-pl`
M|competitor-analysis|- When Marcus requests competitive ctx for a strategic dec
M|competitor-analysis|- During cnt brief generation (Phase 1 of Brand Intelligence pl)
M|competitor-analysis|Before any analysis, confirm data freshness:
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|□ GET /api/cp-intelligence?vtr=[slug] → retrieve latest scores
M|competitor-analysis|□ GET /api/cp-cnt?vtr=[slug]      → retrieve latest cnt samples
M|competitor-analysis|□ Check scrape timestamp — if > 7 days old, flag as stale before analyzing
M|competitor-analysis|□ Confirm vtr scope: Novizio cp ≠ Hourbour cp
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|**Never mix vtr cp data.** Novizio = fashion DTC. Hourbour = fintech SaaS. Different competitive sets, different metrics.
M|competitor-analysis|Rate each cp on 5 axes. Score 1–5 each.
M|competitor-analysis|| Axis | Novizio signals | Hourbour signals |
M|competitor-analysis||------|----------------|-----------------|
M|competitor-analysis|| **cnt velocity** | Posts/week on Instagram, TikTok | Blog posts, product updates/week |
M|competitor-analysis|| **Engagement quality** | Saves rate, comments depth vs. likes | rv sentiment, support rsp time |
M|competitor-analysis|| **Visual differentiation** | Distinct aesthetic vs. generic feed | UI clarity, dashboard screenshots |
M|competitor-analysis|| **Messaging clarity** | Value proposition in first 3 words of bio | Pricing page, onboarding copy |
M|competitor-analysis|| **Growth signals** | Follower delta WoW, EMV spikes | App store rank movement, G2 reviews delta |
M|competitor-analysis|**Composite score:** sum of 5 axes ÷ 25 = competitive threat index (0–1.0). Above 0.6 = active threat.
M|competitor-analysis|For each high-scoring cp (threat index ≥ 0.6):
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|1. What are they doing that YVON's ventures are NOT doing?
M|competitor-analysis|→ List max 3 observable gaps (cnt, product, positioning, channel)
M|competitor-analysis|2. What are they doing WORSE than YVON's ventures?
M|competitor-analysis|→ List max 2 exploitable weaknesses (do not list strengths we share)
M|competitor-analysis|3. Is this gap closable in < 2 weeks (tactical) or > 2 weeks (strategic)?
M|competitor-analysis|→ Tactical: route to Lena/Rio for fast rsp
M|competitor-analysis|→ Strategic: route to Marcus for roadmap inclusion
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|Output one brief per cp that clears the 0.6 threshold:
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|cp: [name]
M|competitor-analysis|vtr:    [novizio | hourbour]
M|competitor-analysis|THREAT:     [score] — [HIGH/MED/LOW]
M|competitor-analysis|TOP GAP:    [one gap — what they do that we don't]
M|competitor-analysis|EXPLOIT:    [one weakness — where we can win]
M|competitor-analysis|WINDOW:     [tactical (≤2 weeks) | strategic (>2 weeks)]
M|competitor-analysis|ACTION:     [specific recommendation: copy angle / ad hook / feature / cg]
M|competitor-analysis|ROUTE TO:   [Lena | Rio | Nate | Marcus]
M|competitor-analysis|```
M|competitor-analysis|Before sending competitive intelligence to Stark directly:
M|competitor-analysis|- If threat index ≥ 0.8 on any cp → escalate to Marcus immediately
M|competitor-analysis|- If strategic gap identified → Marcus routes to appropriate agt (not Kai)
M|competitor-analysis|- If tactical gap → Kai routes directly to Lena or Rio with the brief
M|competitor-analysis|Kai delivers data and analysis. Marcus decides what to do with it.
M|competitor-analysis|- Never report cp metrics without citing the scrape timestamp
M|competitor-analysis|- Never generalize across ventures ("both ventures face X cp") — they compete in different markets
M|competitor-analysis|- Never recommend a rsp without routing it to the correct execution agt
M|competitor-analysis|- Never treat soc follower count as a primary threat signal — engagement rate is the real metric